That this scaling should be universal readily follows from the fact that for very fast quenches, the perturbation does not have time to propagate far from the boundary before the quench concludes. Since the near boundary region of many holographically relevant spacetimes is asymptotically AdS, abrupt quenches are indifferent to the IR features of the geometry distinguishing different holographic spacetimes.

